The Pharmacy (Approved)  informational field used when Other Payer-Patient
Responsibility Amount (352-NQ) or Patient Pay Amount (5Ø5-F5) is used for
reimbursement. Amount is equal to contracted or reimbursable amount for product
being dispensed.
The Pharmacy (Approved)  informational field used when Other Payer-Patient
Responsibility Amount (352-NQ) or Patient Pay Amount (5Ø5-F5) is used for
reimbursement. Amount is equal to contracted or reimbursable dispensing fee for
product being dispensed.
Post Adjudication Ingredient Cost. This field populates with Pharmacy
(approved) ingredient cost if the post-adjudicated field is empty.
Post Adjudication Dispensing Fee Paid. This field populates with
Pharmacy (approved) dispensing fee if the post-adjudicated field is
empty.
Post Adjudication Percentage Sales Tax.  This field populates with
Pharmacy (approved) sales tax if the post-adjudicated field is empty.
Post Adjudication Flat Sales Tax.  This field populates with Pharmacy
(approved) sales tax if the post-adjudicated field is empty.
Post Adjudication Percentage Sales Tax. This field populates with
Pharmacy (approved) sales tax if the post-adjudicated field is empty.
Post Adjudication Patient Pay Amount. This field populates with
Pharmacy (approved) patient pay if the post-adjudicated field is empty.
The patient pay would include copays and all other charges.
Post Adjudication Total Amount Due. This field populates amount due
pharmacy (approved) if the post adjudicated field is empty. Typically,
amount due is calculated as follows: (Ingred Cost + Dispensing Fee +
Tax) – Patient Pay
Post Adjudication Total Withhold Amount. This field populates
Pharmacy (approved) withhold amount if the post adjudicated field is
